The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Creative expositions

 An evening to stimulate the mind of the aesthetically inclined is on the cards, with a variety programme of music, recitation and dance that celebrates life and love in their various aspects. Presented by Chhanda-Bharati, the first part of the programme, Bhalobasar Anyamukh, comprises choreographic renditions of poems, recited and choreographed by Manjusri Roy Chowdhury. Poems to be recited include Kothao kichhu purchhe by Nirendranath Chakraborty, Mone nei ami nijei by Tarapada Roy, Aabar bachhar kuri porey by Jibanananda Das, Path cholte cholte and Mukhe mridu hasi by Sukanta Bhattacharya, Sobar sange bolechhilam and Tumi jante na bujhi by Joy Goswami and Smriti by Manjusri Roy Chowdhury. Anandadhara, a musical presentation, composed by Chandan Roy Chowdhury, has songs that cherish the simple joys of life. Singers: Indrani Sen, Anasua Ghosh and Rupankar. The programme concludes with a discussion on innovations in the field of the audio-visual arts. Participants: Goutam Ghose, Ravi Ojha and Sandip Ray.

 Event: Programme of music, recitation and dance presented by Chhanda-Bharati

 When: Today at 6.30 pm

 Where: Sisir Mancha




